responses.text:
O God! Thou art my God alone;
My heart doth seek Thee, early and late.
In darkest night, in brightest tone,
I cry to Thee, my soul's estate.
My lips, they whisper Thy great name;
My heart, it beats with love's sweet flame.
Thou art my rock, my guiding light;
My shelter from life's plodding night.
I search for Thee, in every place;
I find Thee in each smiling face.
O God! Thou art my God alone;
Forever with Thee, I am made known.

O God! Thou art my God alone;
My soul's deep longing, Thou dost know.
In times of joy, in times of woe;
I turn to Thee, my heart's best flow.
Thy love, it lifts me up on high;
Thy mercy, it catches my wondering eye.
Thou art my comfort, my peaceful nest;
My heart, it finds its sweetest rest.
I'll follow Thee, through all of life;
Through every trial, and every strife.
O God! Thou art my God alone;
My heart, it beats with love, now known.

